title: Troubleshooting and Repair of Diesel Engines
description:
Format: PDF
Genre: Diesel Engines/tutorial
Published: N/A

Book Description: Harness the Latest Tools and Techniques for Troubleshooting and Repairing Virtually Any Diesel Engine Problem

This book includes hundreds of illustrations, schematics, and photographs. Hybrid/diesel engines will comprise nine percent of U.S. auto sales by 2009. The prior edition was used by Caterpillar for its world-wide training program. New to this edition is a new chapter on boosting Performance; new material on bio-diesel fuel and E.U. and U.S. emission standards, new engine mechanics procedures, new developments in air cooled diesels, and more.
